#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn44.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn44.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 44 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 44 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:0.2"
msgid "1. Abyākatavagga "
msgstr "1. The Undeclared Points "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Sabhiyakaccānasutta → sabhiyasuttaṃ (bj) | sabhiyo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn44.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Sabhiyakaccānasutta "
msgstr "11. With Sabhiya Kaccāna "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn44.11:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sabhiyo kaccāno ñātike viharati giñjakāvasathe. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Sabhiya Kaccāna was staying at Nādika in the brick house. "

msgctxt "sn44.11:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yenāyasmā sabhiyo kaccāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sabhiyena kaccānena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to him, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "sn44.11:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako āyasmantaṃ sabhiyaṃ kaccānaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to Sabhiya Kaccāna: "

# NOTE: punctuation incorrect
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:1.4"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho bho, kaccāna, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Kaccāna, does a Realized One exist after death?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:1.5"
msgid "“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, vaccha, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "“Vaccha, this has not been declared by the Buddha.” "

msgctxt "sn44.11:1.6"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:1.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bho kaccāna, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, does a Realized One not exist after death?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:1.8"
msgid "“Etampi kho, vaccha, abyākataṃ bhagavatā: "
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.” "

msgctxt "sn44.11:1.9"
msgid "‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.402, sc2
msgctxt "sn44.11:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho kaccāna, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, does a Realized One both exist and not exist after death?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:2.2"
msgid "“Abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, vaccha, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "“This has not been declared by the Buddha.” "

msgctxt "sn44.11:2.3"
msgid "‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:2.4"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bho kaccāna, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā”ti? "
msgstr "“Well then, does a Realized One neither exist nor not exist after death?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:2.5"
msgid "“Etampi kho, vaccha, abyākataṃ bhagavatā: "
msgstr "“This too has not been declared by the Buddha.” "

msgctxt "sn44.11:2.6"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.1"
msgid "“‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho kaccāna, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "“Master Kaccāna, when asked these questions, you say that this has not been declared by the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.2"
msgid "‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, vaccha, bhagavatā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.3"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.4"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bho kaccāna, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.5"
msgid "‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, vaccha, bhagavatā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.6"
msgid "na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.7"
msgid "‘Kiṃ nu kho, bho kaccāna, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.8"
msgid "‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, vaccha, bhagavatā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.9"
msgid "hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.10"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bho kaccāna, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.11"
msgid "‘etampi kho, vaccha, abyākataṃ bhagavatā—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.12"
msgid "neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.13"
msgid "Ko nu kho, bho kaccāna, hetu, ko paccayo, yenetaṃ abyākataṃ samaṇena gotamenā”ti? "
msgstr "What’s the cause, what’s the reason why this has not been declared by the Buddha?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.14"
msgid "“Yo ca, vaccha, hetu, yo ca paccayo paññāpanāya rūpīti vā arūpīti vā saññīti vā asaññīti vā nevasaññīnāsaññīti vā, so ca hetu, so ca paccayo sabbena sabbaṃ sabbathā sabbaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjheyya. "
msgstr "“In order to describe him as ‘possessing form’ or ‘formless’ or ‘percipient’ or ‘non-percipient’ or ‘neither percipient nor non-percipient’, there must be some cause or reason for doing so. But if that cause and reason were to totally and utterly cease without anything left over, "

msgctxt "sn44.11:3.15"
msgid "Kena naṃ paññāpayamāno paññāpeyya rūpīti vā arūpīti vā saññīti vā asaññīti vā nevasaññīnāsaññīti vā”ti. "
msgstr "how could you describe him in any such terms?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.16"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ pabbajitosi, bho kaccānā”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Kaccāna, how long has it been since you went forth?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.17"
msgid "“Naciraṃ, āvuso, tīṇi vassānī”ti. "
msgstr "“Not long, reverend: three years.” "

# NOTE: See BB and thanissaro for other translations of this idiom.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: bahu, ko pana vādo evaṃ → ko pana vādo eva (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.18"
msgid "“Yassapassa, āvuso, etamettakena ettakameva tampassa bahu, ko pana vādo evaṃ abhikkante”ti. "
msgstr "“Well, you’ve learned a lot already, let alone what lies ahead!” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.19"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn44.11:3.20"
msgid "Abyākatavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.403, sc4
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.1"
msgid "Khemātherī anurādho, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.2"
msgid "sāriputtoti koṭṭhiko; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.3"
msgid "Moggallāno ca vaccho ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.4"
msgid "kutūhalasālānando; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.5"
msgid "Sabhiyo ekādasamanti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn44.11:4.6"
msgid "Abyākatasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on undeclared questions are complete. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.1"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavedanā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.2"
msgid "mātugāmo jambukhādako; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.3"
msgid "Sāmaṇḍako moggallāno, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.4"
msgid "citto gāmaṇi saṅkhataṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.5"
msgid "Abyākatanti dasadhāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.6"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "sn44.11:5.7"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavaggasaṃyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā. "
msgstr "The Book of the Aggregates is finished."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
